'''Rangin Ban''' ({{lang-fa|<U+0631><U+0646><U+06AF><U+064A><U+0646> <U+0628><U+0627><U+0646>}}, also [[Romanize]]d as '''Rang<U+012B>n B<U+0101>n''' and '''Rang<U+012B>n Bon'''; also known as '''Rang<U+012B>n B<U+0101>n-e B<U+0101>zvand''')<ref>{{GEOnet3|-3794347|Rangin Ban}}</ref> is a village in [[Rumeshkhan-e Sharqi Rural District]], [[Rumeshkhan District]], [[Kuhdasht County]], [[Lorestan Province]], [[Iran]]. At the 2006 census, its population was 1,551, in 324 families.<ref>{{IranCensus2006|15}}</ref>  

